{
  "texts": [
    "Through experimental results, the proposed approach demonstrated its efficiency in resolving MAPF problems with the existence of rotation movement.",
    "Another key challenge that can lead to deadlock scenarios is the application of a fully decentralized framework, as it makes it difficult to encourage each agent to act selflessly (Shoham and Leyton-Brown 2008).",
    "Li et al. (2022b) addressed this issue by adopting a hybrid approach that combines decentralized path planning with centralized collision avoidance.",
    "They developed a prioritized communication learning method (PICO), which integrates imitatively learned implicit planning priorities with a communication learning scheme.",
    "PICO has demonstrated its ability in success rates and collision rates, particularly in large-scale scenarios."
  ]
}